Title: The Faddeev-Popov term reviewed

Authors: D. E. Jaramillo(1,2), J. H. Munoz(1,3), A. Zepeda(1) ((1)

CINVESTAV-IPN, Mexico; (2) U. Antioquia, Colombia; (3) U. del Tolima,Colombia)Comments: 6 pages, Latex, to be published en Rev. Mex. Fis

Some textbooks and reports claim that the Jacobian which arises in thediscussion of the Faddeev-Popov method to quantize non-Abelian gauge theoriesand which is given by the derivative of the gauge fixing conditions over thegauge group parameters, is gauge invariant. Other references however prove theopposite. In this brief report we present a discussion about this matter.